src/app/shared/pipes/

‚úÖ 4.1 Generate Pipe
ng generate pipe shared/pipes/roleDisplay

4.2 role-display.pipe.ts
import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from '@angular/core';

@Pipe({
  name: 'roleDisplay'
})
export class RoleDisplayPipe implements PipeTransform {

  transform(value: string): string {
    if (!value) return '';

    return value === 'ADMIN'
      ? 'Administrator'
      : 'Normal User';
  }
}

Q)How do you create a custom pipe in Angular?

‚úÖ Answer

By using @Pipe decorator and implementing PipeTransform.

import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from '@angular/core';

@Pipe({
  name: 'roleDisplay'
})
export class RoleDisplayPipe implements PipeTransform {

  transform(value: string): string {
    if (!value) return '';

    return value === 'ADMIN'
      ? 'Administrator'
      : 'Normal User';
  }
}
Declare Pipe (IMPORTANT)

If module-based:

declarations: [RoleDisplayPipe]

Q)Can pipes accept parameters?

‚úÖ Answer

Yes, pipes can accept parameters after colon.

    <h1>Parameterized Custom Pipes</h1>

    <h4>{{num1|multiplyPipe:2}}</h4>

import { Pipe, PipeTransform } from '@angular/core';

@Pipe({
  name: 'multiplyPipe',
  standalone: true
})
export class MultiplyPipePipe implements PipeTransform {

  transform(value: number,factor:number): number {
    return value * factor;
  }

}


